      "writtenOn": "2020-01-13T18:45:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The logic for this loop has changed, and I think it\u0027s no longer correct:\n\nIt\u0027s always using lvalues.back(), so we\u0027re storing to the last out parameter repeatedly. The old code did that (and then called pop_back), but also iterated the parameters in reverse order. With the way that you\u0027re tracking nextArg here, I think you need something like:\n\n    int lValIndex \u003d 0;\n    for (int i \u003d 0; i \u003c argCount; ++i) {\n        const auto\u0026 param \u003d c.fFunction.fParameters[i];\n        if (param-\u003efModifiers.fFlags \u0026 Modifiers::kOut_Flag) {\n            lvalues[lValIndex++]-\u003estore(nextArg);\n        }\n        nextArg.fIndex +\u003d SlotCount(param-\u003efType);\n    }",
