      "writtenOn": "2020-01-13T18:45:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "kLoopNext used to be issued before kLoopMask here, and I think it\u0027s important. Consider the (pathological) loop:\n\ndo { continue; } while (false);\n\nWith kLoopMask happening first, all lanes get masked off, but then kLoopNext restores them all to active *after* the loop condition is evaluated. Putting kLoopNext first turns any continue\u0027d lanes back on before the condition is evaluated. (This is even more important if there are side-effects in the loop condition expression, although that\u0027s a pretty awkward construct).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1203,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 1205,
        "endChar": 50
      },
      "revId": "f7f0ad5518b0244247341c6e1f74435de3d7400f",
